ne-link\" href=\"https://www.androidcentral.com/phones/prime-day-is-back-next-month-faq-early-deals-and-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-big-sale\" data-before-rewrite-localise=\"https://www.androidcentral.com/phones/prime-day-is-back-next-month-faq-early-deals-and-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-big-sale\"\u003eOctober Prime Day\u003c/a\u003e, I decided to finally bite the bullet and splurge on a 43-inch The Frame TV by Samsung. I’ve had my eye on these smart TVs for a while but wasn’t sure if they were too gimmicky or not. The idea is simple: you take a Samsung smart TV and give it an anti-glare display with a matte finish alongside a super-lightweight construction that sits flat against the wall. Once it’s installed, The Frame TV is supposed to look indistinguishable from a framed painting (when you use Art Mode, of course). I love the idea of not having an ugly TV hanging in my bedroom, and since Amazon is dropping 15% off the 43-inch model, it seemed worth a shot!\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e* Samsung 43-Inch The Frame Series Smart TV:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca data-analytics-id=\"inline-link\" href=\"https://target.georiot.com/Proxy.ashx?tsid=169923\u0026amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Famazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CV9HY4J9%3Fth%3D1%26tag%3Dhawk-future-20%26ascsubtag%3Dac-us-6357714783295020625-20\" data-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CV9HY4J9?th=1\" target=\"_blank\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\" rel=\"sponsored noopener\" data-hl-processed=\"hawklinks\" data-placeholder-url=\"https://target.georiot.com/Proxy.ashx?tsid=169923\u0026amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Famazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CV9HY4J9%3Fth%3D1%26tag%3Dhawk-future-20%26ascsubtag%3Dhawk-custom-tracking-20\" data-google-interstitial=\"false\" data-merchant-name=\"Amazon US\" data-merchant-id=\"1471\" data-merchant-url=\"amazon.com\" data-merchant-network=\"Amazon\"\u003e\u003cdel\u003e$997\u003c/del\u003e \u003cstrong\u003e$847 at Amazon\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"jerry-hildenbrand-senior-editor-google-and-android-ecosystem-3\"\u003eJerry Hildenbrand, Senior Editor - Google and Android Ecosystem\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cfigure data-bordeaux-image-check=\"\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-320-80.jpg.webp 320w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-480-80.jpg.webp 480w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-650-80.jpg.webp 650w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-970-80.jpg.webp 970w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-1024-80.jpg.webp 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-1200-80.jpg.webp 1200w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1000px) 970px, calc(100vw - 40px)\"/\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-320-80.jpg\" alt=\"Creality K1C 3D Printer\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-320-80.jpg 320w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-480-80.jpg 480w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-650-80.jpg 650w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-970-80.jpg 970w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-1024-80.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH-1200-80.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1000px) 970px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" loading=\"lazy\" data-original-mos=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH.jpg\" data-pin-media=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Fd4fycXNVCVAUsYqWBBrdH.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cfigcaption itemprop=\"caption description\"\u003e\u003cspan itemprop=\"copyrightHolder\"\u003e(Image credit: Creality)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eI told myself I wasn\u0026#39;t going to buy anything except some rechargeable batteries on Prime Day, but I was wrong. I grabbed my batteries so I could play in the dark with my flashlight.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e* Rechargeable 3.7V 3500mAh 18650 Battery 2-Pack:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca data-analytics-id=\"inline-link\" href=\"https://target.georiot.com/Proxy.ashx?tsid=169923\u0026amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Famazon.com%2FBENKIA-Rechargeable-Battery-3500mAh-Flashlight%2Fdp%2FB0CJJKH4P2%3Ftag%3Dhawk-future-20%26ascsubtag%3Dac-us-5977504484583848919-20\" data-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/BENKIA-Rechargeable-Battery-3500mAh-Flashlight/dp/B0CJJKH4P2\" target=\"_blank\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\" rel=\"sponsored noopener\" data-hl-processed=\"hawklinks\" data-placeholder-url=\"https://target.georiot.com/Proxy.ashx?tsid=169923\u0026amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Famazon.com%2FBENKIA-Rechargeable-Battery-3500mAh-Flashlight%2Fdp%2FB0CJJKH4P2%3Ftag%3Dhawk-future-20%26ascsubtag%3Dhawk-custom-tracking-20\" data-google-interstitial=\"false\" data-merchant-name=\"Amazon US\" data-merchant-id=\"1471\" data-merchant-url=\"amazon.com\" data-merchant-network=\"Amazon\"\u003e\u003cdel\u003e$19\u003c/del\u003e \u003cstrong\u003e$15 at Amazon\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI also took a chance and bought a pack of bamboo men\u0026#39;s underwear. I\u0026#39;ve heard a lot of good things about them and how much nicer they are than cotton, but they\u0026#39;re crazy expensive so I never wanted to try them. Saving 20% was enough to make me go for it.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e* Bamboo Cool Breathable Men\u0026#39;s Boxer Briefs 6 Pack:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca data-analytics-id=\"inline-link\" href=\"https://target.georiot.com/Proxy.ashx?tsid=169923\u0026amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Famazon.com%2FBAMBOO-COOL-Breathable-Comfortsoft-Moisture-Wicking%2Fdp%2FB0CGLYHF6G%3Ftag%3Dhawk-future-20%26ascsubtag%3Dac-us-1312448150961394670-20\" data-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/BAMBOO-COOL-Breathable-Comfortsoft-Moisture-Wicking/dp/B0CGLYHF6G?\" target=\"_blank\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\" rel=\"sponsored noopener\" data-hl-processed=\"hawklinks\" data-placeholder-url=\"https://target.georiot.com/Proxy.ashx?tsid=169923\u0026amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Famazon.com%2FBAMBOO-COOL-Breathable-Comfortsoft-Moisture-Wicking%2Fdp%2FB0CGLYHF6G%3Ftag%3Dhawk-future-20%26ascsubtag%3Dhawk-custom-tracking-20\" data-google-interstitial=\"false\" data-merchant-name=\"Amazon US\" data-merchant-id=\"1471\" data-merchant-url=\"amazon.com\" data-merchant-network=\"Amazon\"\u003e\u003cdel\u003e$52\u003c/del\u003e \u003cstrong\u003e$42 at Amazon\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI also spent way too much money and did one of those things that would keep me awake at night, but I couldn\u0026#39;t say no. I got \u003ca data-analytics-id=\"inline-link\" href=\"https://www.androidcentral.com/accessories/this-creality-3d-printer-is-usd130-off-and-works-from-my-phone-so-im-buying-it\" data-before-rewrite-localise=\"https://www.androidcentral.com/accessories/this-creality-3d-printer-is-usd130-off-and-works-from-my-phone-so-im-buying-it\"\u003ethe 3D printer that\u0026#39;s been in my save for later list\u003c/a\u003e for a few months while I could save $130. I\u0026#39;ve been wanting to print with carbon fiber a little more, and I wanted to try a plug-and-play model that works via a smartphone app. The Creality K1C came highly recommended so I did the thing.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e* Creality K1C 3D Printer:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca data-analytics-id=\"inline-link\" href=\"https://target.georiot.com/Proxy.ashx?tsid=169923\u0026amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Famazon.com%2FCreality-K1C-High-Speed-Clog-Free-Filaments%2Fdp%2FB0D9BGHHKF%3Ftag%3Dhawk-future-20%26ascsubtag%3Dac-us-1884144335598059434-20\" data-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/Creality-K1C-High-Speed-Clog-Free-Filaments/dp/B0D9BGHHKF\" target=\"_blank\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\" re